   <note>A letter from Silas Dinsmoor addressed to the Honorable James Robertson, Esquire. Dinsmoor relates there will be a council of Cherokees discussing Indians killed on Stone River the prior year. Dinsmoor asks for a statement of facts about the killings to inform his participation in the talks. Dinsmoor also asked Robertson to provide a member of his office at the meetings. He ends the letter with a general assurance of the Indian people`s desire for peace.</note>
